<br>
Let's take this scenario:<br>
<br>
You're &quot;black&quot;. Your father's black, your mother's black, you follow your roots to being purely African. No mixing, no interracial relationships. Fully black and proud. However, your ancestors were taken as slaves from Namibia to Cuba. Unmixed, yet living in Cuba for over a century. You are classified, by Americans, as hispanic.<br>
<br>
You're &quot;white&quot;. Your father's white, your mother's white, you follow your roots to being purely European. No mixing, no interracial relationships. Fully white and proud. However, your ancestors were slaveowners from Spain living in Argentina. Unmixed, yet living in Argentina for over a century. You are classified, by Americans, as hispanic.<br>
<br>
Now, for the life of me I cannot fathom WHY 2 distinct people are classified in the same race, ONLY based on their language. Their culture isn't even the same, as much as you are led to believe on television, it isn't. Period. &quot;Hispanic&quot;, in ever sense of the word, is someone who's culture is derived from Spain. This does NOT classify one's race, and neither does &quot;Latin&quot; or &quot;Latino&quot;, which I find even worse. Look up who the Latin people were and tell me how you can call an un-mixed Aztec descendant from Mexico Latin. Back in my academy I was always taught that races were classified by their cranial structures and other physical characteristics, and ethnic groups broken down from races even further categorized by culture. How an African and a European can be subclassed together is beyond me, they're two different people from two different cultures.<br>
<br>
Hell, I take offense to being called &quot;white&quot;.  That's not me. I don't like hispanic either, that isn't a race. Want to give me a race? Give me Iberian. Or, even broader, give me Mediterranean, along with the other sea-borderers like the Italians. Non-American Italians would punch you in the face if you call them &quot;white&quot;, by the way. My Italian buddy was filling out forms when he was coming to school in America with me, he gets to the race portion and tells me, &quot;what should I put? I'm Euro with olive skin and my language comes from the same as yours... should I just shade them all?&quot;<br>
<br>
Eninziel.<br>
